  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Ethical Recruitment and Fair Labour Practices in Garment and Footwear Supply Chain (Phase II)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In September 2019, IOM supported an international apparel and footwear company to implement the American Apparel and Footwear Association (AAFA) / Fair Labour Association (FLA) Industry Commitment to Responsible Recruitment. The partnership project aimed at reducing unethical recruitment and exploitative labour practices in the company&apos;s supply chains in Asia through strengthening company&apos;s management system for recruitment and employment of migrant workers. Specifically, IOM supported the company to develop internal recruitment standards and guidelines in line with international standards on ethical recruitment and a capacity-building programme to the company team on forced labour and human trafficking.</narrative>
  </description>
